 style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Predominantly focusing on the convenience and supermarket sector, the key aim of this business is to create a strengthened co-operative retail offer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">that will generate sustainable profits and provide improved services to members and customers.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Amongst its other wholly-owned businesses are the UK’s number one funeral services provider, the third largest pharmacy chain, a growing legal services operatio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">n and a major general insurer.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">As well as having clear financial and operational objectives, the Group, which operates 4,500 outlets and employs approaching</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">90,000 people, is a recognised leader for its social goals and community-led programmes</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Co-operative Group is committed to playing its part in helping to reduce the numbers of single use </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">carrier bags </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">given out in stores</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">. Our own progress</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">, made possible by the efforts of our customers and store staff,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> in this area has led the market.  The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Co-operative Group has reduced the numbers of single use bags distributed in our food stores </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">by 64</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">% since 2006</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> (when industry-wide reduction targets were first set)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> without the necessity of charging, and has a target to make further reductions.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Sale of Co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">mpostable Carrier Bags in Co-operative Stores</span></h1><h2 style="margin:10pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">To date we have sold compostable carrier bags in 111 stores across England (and 108 in Scotland).  These bags are fully certified to BS EN 13432 and also carry the AFOR home compostability logo.  We </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ell </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">around </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5.2 million of these bags each year.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">These bags have been sold with a specific end-of-life purpose in areas where that purpose is valid – food waste caddy liner use in areas where the local authority will accept the bags.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The compostable carrier bags, which carry the seedling logo are made from a combination of natural materials. They a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">re strong enough to carry home the weekly shopping, including heavy, bulky items such as milk and potatoes.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">We have controlled the areas in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> which these bags are sold, so that we can avoid areas where there may be concerns about their acceptability in composting and anaerobic digestion purely by responding to the acceptance/non-acceptance of the local authority.  This approach </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">has provided u</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">with the flexibility to use current technology to support local authority food waste collections while continuing to develop improved technological solutions.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">We have had positive feedback on this initiative from council environment services as it support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s their food waste collections and helps to encourage greater resident engagement.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">In addition, because we are selling these bags to support food waste collection, and because we are encouraging greater resident engagement in food waste collection through</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> this, this means that the environmental benefit of selling these bags goes far beyond the replacement of polythene single-use bags.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">We have recently announced (15 January 2013) that compostable carrier bags, will be made available to even more customers,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> bringing the total number of around Co-operative food stores offering these bags to around 400.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">This extension in availability marks the first time a large-scale food retailer has given shoppers over such a wide area the option of alternative carrier bag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s with a specific second use.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">We have been motivated to extend the scheme because of the success of the trials that we have run to date. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Compostable Bags will be available in stores </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">covering 81 local authority areas with food recycling schemes which requi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">re householders to use compostable bags for food waste.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Co-operative also believes that the new compostable carrier bags could play a vital role in encouraging more people to recycle food waste.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">  The Co-operative is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">the only major food retailer in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> UK to offer carrier bags which are also compostable and carry the seedling logo. Our aim is to enable our customers to recycle more of the products they buy from us – from the leftover food and packaging, right through to the bag they use to carry their s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">hopping </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">home.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The new compostable carrier bags are being introduced in The Co-operative Food stores in the following local authority areas:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Aylesbury Vale, Barnet, Basildon, Bath &amp; North East Somerset, Braintree, Brent, Brentwood, Bristol, Bromley, Camden</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">, Cheltenham, Chiltern, Chorley, Christchurch, Colchester, Cotswold, Derby, Ealing, East Devon, East Dorset, East Northamptonshire, East Staffordshire, Eastleigh, Elmbridge, Enfield, Epping Forest, Epsom and Ewell, Greenwich, Guildford, Harlow, High Peak, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Islington, Knowsley, Lambeth, Lancaster, Lewes, Merton, Mid Devon, Mole Valley, North Devon, North Dorset, North Somerset, Norwich, Oxford City, Purbeck, Reigate and Banstead, Richmond-upon-Thames, Rochford, Rugby, Runnymeade, Sandwell, Sefton, South Oxfor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">dshire, South Buckinghamshire, South Gloucestershire, South Ribble, Spelthorne, Staffordshire Moorlands, Stevenage, Stratford-on-Avon, Suffolk Coastal, Surrey Heath, Tameside, Tandridge, Teignbridge, Tendring, Tewkesbury, Thurrock, Torbay, Vale of White Ho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">rse, Waltham Forest, Warwick, Waveney, Waverley, West Berkshire, West Dorset, West Oxfordshire, Windsor and Maidenhead, Woking, Wychavon, Wycombe.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Possible Exemption from Charging for Single Use Carrier Bags for Compostable Bags</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Whilst we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">welcome </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">an exemption for biodegradable bags in certain circumstances we believe that without caveats an exemption will result in a direct substitution of conventional plastic single use bags for biodegradable bags.  Not requiring biodegradable bags to be charged f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">or will perpetuate the problems of excessive distribution and inefficient use of resources – it will just substitute one environmental problem with another.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">The Co-operative sells compostable bags, certified to EN 13432 and the new AFOR home composting st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">andard, at 6p each.  These are used initially to carry shopping home but then are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">reused</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> for local authority food waste collection (and home composting).  This allows local authorities in England to make use of this potentially valuable support mechanism f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">or food waste collection.  We have had only positive feedback on this initiative from local authority environment services.  As additional local authorities introduce food waste collection, low-cost accessible provision of caddy-liners in schemes such as t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">his will only serve to improve resident engagement while minimising increased burdens on local authority budgets.  The fact that we only sell the bags in areas where the local authority will accept them means that management of their suitability for anaero</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">bic digestion is built in.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">14 January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>